</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,258,822]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,296,258,283]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
Forewings 2.0 times longer than wide, length in male 
<quantity box="[904,1042,258,282]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="4.2" valueMin="3.8">3.8–4.2 mm</quantity>
. Colour light brown; apical portion of abdomen of male (except genitalia) bright red. Forewings powdered; most parts uniformly infuscated; slightly darker marks around M-Ms4 and R-Rs1 forks; lighter near apical margin; a clear area around apices of Ms1a, Ms2, Ms3 and Ms4; veins orange-brown. Hindwings uniformly infuscated, veins orange-brown. Rostrum surpassing hind coxae; subantennal processes connected to margins of facial carinae. Forewings with Sc+R fork just before middle of wing; Ms1 branched just distad of apex of basal median cell, a triangle at base of Ms1. Male genital styles broadening towards end which is truncate; proximal dorsal process short, distal dorsal process elongated, both well separated. Aedeagus with apical portion spatulate; on the right side two elongated, dorsal lobes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1134,546,571]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1436,258,822]" box="[199,1134,546,571]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
