<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,547,571]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Etymology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The species name is a Latin adjective (
<emphasis box="[775,981,547,570]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zelazny &amp; Webb" authorityYear="2011" box="[775,890,547,570]" class="Insecta" family="Derbidae" genus="Levu" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nocturnus">nocturnus</taxonomicName>
, -a, -um
</emphasis>
= nocturnal).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
